data.title: Worst restaurant in MN
data.text:
Unfortunately there isn't a negative rating option.

Went for lunch, they took my money and then locked the doors and ignored me.  Asked for my food twice, only to be ignored.

Finally asked for a refund and the doors to be unlocked.

Will never return.

data.title: Authentic
data.text: Nice to find a place that serves Mexican tacos, not Tex Mex. In other words, no shredded iceberg lettuce or grated american cheese on everything. Just basic taco ingredients, meat, onion, cilantro, queso. Wide variety of choices available also.

data.title: Great food and service.
data.text: The food and service here is top notch. Too bad the work day wasn't over since I'd have loved to have one of several local craft beers they had on tap. 4 stars only because I'm sort of a traditionalist when it comes to tacos.

data.title: Change of pace but overpriced
data.text: Rusty taco is a good change of pace from Chipotle for two reasons - they have a big menu and it's not Chipotle.  Prices are a bit high at $3 per taco.  For a family of four that adds up to a $40 do need in a hurry.  For that price there are sit down restaurants you could eat at.  We had a couple of mistakes on our order on our most recent visit which they fixed, but not before hassling us first.

data.title: A taco for every day!
data.text:
Don't let the location or casual exterior put you off. This street style taco joint is fantastic. 

First visit just the other day found the place packed with a long line waiting. Oh yes, it's very popular with the locals! The line moved quickly as the staff danced fluidly through the orders. Grab a bite, enjoy it at the taco counter where you can watch the delicious tastiness being prepared. You can even enjoy a margarita or beer with your  tacos. Meats cooked in house. Guacamole prepared on site. Even the salsas, I'm told, are prepared fresh each day.

This is not a place for a large gathering or a "working lunch" unless you come in well past noon. The east wall has 2 garage door style windows that opened up onto a patio. I imagine it's quite pleasant during the warmer months.

I look forward to many more trips to the Rusty Taco.

data.title: Great for a casual bite
data.text: Good food, fun atmosphere!  Something on the menu for every taco taste plus beverages for the kids and adults.

data.title: Can't beat the price for quick, healthy food
data.text: The food is good, the menu is simple...tacos, chips, etc.  Breakfast taco and black bean tacos are very good.  Chips and salsa are free refill.  The ingredients always taste fresh, and you can watch it all being prepared.  The patio is as great place to hang out as well.

data.title: Great food at a great price
data.text: We went as a group to this fast casual restaurant. We each ordered and sat down. The employees were very friendly and we had our food pretty quickly. I opted for the fish tacos and they did not disappoint. Some of the others in my group were a bit more adventurous in their menu choices but it was all eaten, with no leftovers. We all agreed it was delicious and wished we had one in our respective home towns. Highly recommended.

data.title: Really good!
data.text: I love going here.  Very affordable and much better than going to a fast food restaurant.  I get #13 Texican Taco (spiced beef, tomato, lettuce and cheese.   We also get the chips and salsa - excellent. And of course a Margarita - which they say is made with cheap tequila, but it is good.   They also have breakfast tacos which I am dying to try sometime.

data.title: Good taco
data.text: Stopped in for a quick lunch.... It was busy but line moved quickly. It was hard to decide what to have but I liked my choices. Would highly recommend the chips and queso. I had the shredded pork taco and a shredded beef taco. They were very full of meat and really tasty

data.title: Great alternative to fast food while still being fast
data.text: In the past, my only experience with Rusty Taco had been their food truck.  So we decided we needed to try out there store front.  While the food was still AMAZING, the dining area is not inviting. It was raining the day we went, so I can't speak to the patio seating other than it exists.  My recommendation would be to stop in and get your food to go.  Not a great space to enjoy a meal with friends.

data.title: A bit overhyped
data.text: Tastier than the bell, but 3 tacos fast for $8. Not worth standing long in line for. Soda is $2. Did not try the $5 margarita.

data.title: Great taco's and dog friendly
data.text:
My husband and I enjoyed some delicious taco's on the patio with our two dogs. We sampled 4 different tacos and even though they were small the ingredients were fresh and flavorful. The hot sauce was hotter than I would have expected but still great - I love spicy food. 
Didn't give 5 stars because we paid 17.00 for food we picked up at the counter, the tacos were small, and the chips were not fresh.

data.title: Cheap Food, but Great Taste
data.text: This place is fast food that tastes authentic!  You pay per taco!  They also have beer and $5 Margaritas!  My Baja Shrimp Taco and Chips and Quesso came to only $6.44!  They also have a nice outdoor patio!  The food was done super fast! I will be back!

data.title: A bit salty for me
data.text: Soft tacos weren't anything to write home about. I had a Texican Taco, chicken fajita taco, and Nachos.  Texican taco was pretty good with lots of cheese. The Chicken Fajita taco was quite as good. Chicken was dry. Nachos were way to salty for my taste. Good cold beer was the highlight. The old style rock-n-roll made for a great atmosphere. Overall, not a bad experience for a fast food joint.

data.title: I hate soft shell tacos......but
data.text:
these are really good! 

As one of those people to whom cilantro usually tastes like soap I was a bit concerned when I saw it in so many items.  Was this going to be an experience like having my mouth washed out? Nope! I don't know the difference between what Rusty Taco uses and that 'other giant burrito restaurant', but no issues for the cilantro disdainful here.

This is a quick taco place - Charlie Trotter isn't managing it, the ingredients weren't selected by a shaman at an indigenous co-op, nobody in the kitchen studied abroad in Oaxaca to bring back secrets.

The beef, cheese, lettuce tacos are nothing special.  If you want run-of-the-mill volume, save your money and go to Taco Bell.  But if you want to try a different type of taco - the roasted pork, the beef fajita, the brisket, and especially the fried chicken taco are very enjoyable.  Add your choice of there own sauces which are light and taste fresher than most and you won't be disappointed.

And, you can't sit outside with a beer or margarita while you enjoy your tacos at those other places.

data.title: never met a taco I didnt like
data.text: Taco is in the name and tacos are what they do, and they do them well! A good selection of creative items, quick, relatively inexpensive, a nice environment, even serve breakfast tacos, what else to say? I went there 2 days in a row and i'll be back!

data.title: Just OK unfortunately
data.text: We were excited to try it but a few things weren't as expected so I can't give it a great review.  Asked for a couple of additions/subtractions (add avocado, no cilantro) and neither order was correct.

data.title: I had better!!
data.text: We tried this restaurant after a local TV station name it the best in Twine Cities. I was expecting an exceptional Mexican tacos, and it was rather a mediocre taco food track. I was not happy with the menu, portions or taste.

data.title: Not What I Expected...
data.text: I was not happy with the portions considering the money I spent.  The amount of taco filling you get is considerably less than what you'd get at Taco Bell.I don't care for their choice of tortillas either.  I went once and haven't been back.
